ing of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Vaughan was born in 1548, in Glamorgan, Wales. She married Phillip Bowen about 1569, in Glamorgan, Wales. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1604, in her hometown, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1548–1604":"1548–1604","1544–1603":"1544–1603","1570–Male":"1570–Surnud","1574–1633":"1574–1633","1633":"1633","1544":"1544","about 1569":"umbes 1569","1574":"1574","1570":"1570","about 1570":"umbes 1570","1604":"1604","1548":"1548","1603":"1603","Slade, Oxwich, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Slade, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Slade, Glamorgan, Wales":"Slade, Glamorgan, Wales","Oxwich, Glamorganshire, Wales  --  or  --  Slade, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Oxwich, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Kilvey, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fi":{"1548–1604":"1548–1604","1544–1603":"1544–1603","1570–Male":"1570–Kuollut","1574–1633":"1574–1633","1633":"1633","1544":"1544","about 1569":"noin 1569","1574":"1574","1570":"1570","about 1570":"noin 1570","1604":"1604","1548":"1548","1603":"1603","Slade, Oxwich, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Slade, Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Slade, Glamorgan, Wales":"Slade, Glamorgan, Wales","Oxwich, Glamorganshire, Wales  --  or  --  Slade, Glamorganshire, Wales":"Oxwich, Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","Kilvey, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fr":{"1548–1604":"1548–1604","1544–1603":"1544–1603","1570–Male":"1570–Décédé","1574–1633":"1574–1633","1633":"1633","15